Albert Kuo

I am a 5th year biostatistics PhD student at Johns Hopkins University working with Cristian Tomasetti and Stephanie Hicks to develop statistical methods in the fields of cancer and genomics. Previously, I interned at Amazon as a data scientist in 2021 and received my bachelor’s in mathematics and statistics from the University of Chicago in 2016.

In my free time, I enjoy writing on my blog, reading, and playing music.
